Scripted button. When clicked, the triangle rotates downward and the window expands to a specified height. Clicking on the triangle again rotates the triangle back to the right and restores the stack to a specified height.

The button resizes the stack in which it is placed to the sizes contained in two custom properties stored on the button:

cUndisclosedStackHeight
cDisclosedStackHeight

The button references 5 images. The ids for these images are stored in the following custom properties set on the button:

cIcon
cHilitedIcon
cIntermediateIcon
cDisclosedHilitedIcon
cDisclosed

The icon of the button can be set to either of the following custom properties for a disabled appearance:

cDisabledIcon
cDisclosedDisabledIcon

Note that this control requires the "Revolution Icons" image library to be tranferred to your stack using Distribution Builder when you are preparing your stack for distribution.